social_posts.post_text:
🎉 Good things come in threes! 🎉 We're thrilled to share 3 HUGE announcements with you, SB Nation!

1️⃣ "Some Girls Do" has officially reached platinum status! 🌟

2️⃣ Our Greatest Hits album has also achieved platinum status! 🏆 

3️⃣ Ahead of our upcoming 40th anniversary as a travelin' band, we're excited to announce that we have reunited with @curbrecords! 🎵📝 This renewed partnership means the race is on for more music and memories with you!

As always, we continue to thank God for YOU. We’re so grateful to every one of you out there for taking the dirt road with us all these years! 🎉🎶 

#SawyerBrown #CountryMusic #40thAnniversary #CurbRecords
Some girls don’t like boys like us … but some girls do. 😎

We can’t wait to see YOU! Let us know which shows you are going to this summer!

ONANCOCK, VA - Hope you're ready to have a good time! 

We're ready to STEP THAT STEP with every one of you at the ESVA Chamber Fest tonight!

🚨 We’ve got some HUGE NEWS! 🚨

We are so excited to officially announce “Get Me to the Stage on Time.” 🎤

The film gives a behind-the-scenes look at how we’ve traveled millions of miles, made 24 albums, and played 6,000 shows thanks to a legion of fans we could always count on! And we aren’t even close to being done yet. 🎥

“Get Me To The Stage On Time” will premiere as part of the Nashville Film Festival on Sunday, October 1. Following the film, we are performing live with some special guests! 😉

Tap the link in our bio to BUY TICKETS!

#sawyerbrown #sawyerbrownmovie #sawyerbrowndocumentary #music #musicdocumentary #musicdoc #90s #90scountry #newmovies #blakeshelton #dollyparton #dierksbentley

This may be our most exciting news EVER! 🤯

We have a new film called “Get Me To The Stage On Time” coming to the @nashfilmfest Oct. 1! 

We’re so excited to share our story with all of you, and want to say a special thanks to @Billboard for helping us debut the official trailer for the film!

Be sure to check our bio for all the info you need about “Get Me To The Stage On Time.”

social_posts.post_text:
We've got some BIG things coming YOUR way! Hope y'all are ready 😉

9.29.23

Basically, what we're saying is ... @ChrisStapleton has us to thank. 😂

Okay ... maybe not so much! 😆 

But we do love hearing him sing. Here are our favorite songs by one of the greatest Country singers ever.

Some girls don't like boys like us ... awww but some girls do! 

We love performing this song and look forward to performing it again tonight for YOU Oxford, AL! 🙏

We’re BACK, baby!

New music coming your way next FRIDAY! The song, “Under This Ole Hat,” was produced by @blakeshelton ... but don’t hold that against us 😂

Tap the link in our bio to pre-save / pre-add 🤠
Oxford, AL/Oxford Performing Arts Center—Oh. Heck. Yeah! The weekend started early with y’all tonight! So much fun—thanks for that Sold Out show!

If we ask nicely ... will you PLEASE come have an absolutely rockin' time with us tonight?! 🙏

We're playing at The Martin Centre in Douglas, GA and could NOT be more thankful for the chance to play some live music for you all! 🎸
Douglas, GA/The Martin Centre Preservation Company—Y’all were so much fun last night—thanks! What a beautiful theatre! And don’t even get us started on how good the food was, too!
Love songs in the '80s really hit different!
Next time you see a farmer ... tell 'em THANK YOU!

💥 We’ve got a big surprise for y’all 💥

“Under This Ole Hat” is available NOW ... but that’s not all! 

The new single is the first release from our upcoming album “Desperado Troubadours,” which comes out in March 2024! The project was produced by @blakeshelton and we’re so excited for y’all to hear it!

Tap the link in our bio to stream “Under This Ole Hat” now!

#sawyerbrown #newmusicfriday #countrymusic #underthisolehat #desperadotroubadours

WHAT A NIGHT!

"Get Me To The Stage On Time," the film about our band's 40 years (and counting) in Country Music, premiered last night at the @FranklinTheatre for the @nashfilmfest!

The entire evening was more than fun than we could have ever imagined. And, we even got to pull off a big surprise for the fans by bringing out our two former bandmates, Bobby Randall and Duncan Cameron, who were so instrumental in the Sawyer Brown story! 

For all of those who weren't able to make it, we'll be sharing more pics and videos from the premiere soon!

📸: @michaelgomezphotography

We're starting this month's shows tomorrow night at the Colonial Theater in Idaho Falls, and we have several more gigs that we're incredibly excited about.

Will we be seeing YOU at any of our shows this month?!

We still can’t believe this happened!

At the start of October, the film about our band’s life story, “Get Me To The Stage On Time,” premiered as part of the Nashville Film Festival. We even put together a special performance that has NEVER happened before in the history of our band by bringing back two former band members, Bobby Randall and Duncan Cameron!

It was a night we’ll never forget … and as always, we Thank God For You for making it all possible. 

P.S. For all the folks who have been asking, the doc will be available on streaming early next year. More details to come, so stay tuned! 🙏
